{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, transparent cross-cultural dialog on cerebral organoid research will be vital for developing ethically grounded, universally acceptable policies.",
    "The National Academies report (National Academies of Sciences, Engineering, and Medicine, 2021) suggests that these issues require discussion among people with different perspectives.",
    "They also highlight the importance of engaging with the public, understanding and addressing their concerns, and linking research to important unmet needs, such as the need for treatments for brain diseases.",
    "Existing surveys reveal general support among publics for brain organoid research aimed at reducing suffering from disease, accompanied by concerns about consciousness, chimeras, and commercialization (Haselager et al., 2020; Steinsbekk et al., 2021).",
    "However, most laypersons lack awareness about organoids, and perceptions are readily shaped by hype or unrealistic media portrayals (Haselager et al., 2020)."
  ]
}